What is OS?
-> Operating system is an computer software program that is "used to manage our computer hardware resources 
and provides an environment for our applications to execute".



What is Linux?
-> "Linux is open source operating system based on the linux kernel" which anyone can modify and distribute.

What is kernel?
-> Kernel is "master computer software program which manages the hardware resources or interacts with hardware component" or "the core component of an OS".
- Humans cannot understand the language of kernel.

linux is kernel using which many linux os have been released and these releases are known as "Flavors"
For example - slackware, centOS, ubuntu, fedore, debian, archlinux etc.

what is hardware?
-> The hardware essentially consists of CPU, RAM, and Hard disk(ROM) with supporting electronic chips(chip set)
